commentPostTextItems.html: With great centuries from McCullum and Marshal New Zealand have posted their highest ODI total of 402 and the 6th highest ever. What do Ireland have in reply?

The teams are due out at 3.00pm local time and the wind has died down from this morning and the sun is shining. The wicket is set up for batsmen and the outfield is quick but can the Irish get anywhere near New Zealand's total.
Tomorrow sees Ireland take on Scotland and for those with a chance to get down to Aberdeen tickets can be purchased at the gate for £15(concessions £10)

milestones.description: Marshall and McCullum's 274-run partnership is NZ's highest for the 1st wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 204 between Fleming and Lou Vincent
This is the highest match aggregate (514) involving teams New Zealand & Ireland in ODIs
New Zealand's 291-run win against Ireland is the largest margin of victory in terms of runs in ODIs, beating 210-run win against U.S.A.
Marshall and McCullum's 274-run partnership is NZ's highest for any wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 204 between Lou Vincent and Fleming
Peter Connell has conceded the most runs in an innings (95) in ODIs for IRE, going past John Mooney's record of 79
McCullum has broken the record for most sixes in an innings (10) in ODIs for NZ, going past Lou Vincent's 9

stories.title: New Zealand crush hapless Irish
stories.subTitle: Ireland v New Zealand, Tri-series, Aberdeen
stories.summary: It was a day of records and near-records at Mannofield Park in Aberdeen, as a rampant New Zealand team totally outclassed a threadbare Ireland by a record ODI margin of 290 runs

stories.title: Buoyant New Zealand head north
stories.subTitle: Ireland v New Zealand, Tri-series, Aberdeen
stories.summary: New Zealand can't quite begin their long journey home yet, and with the taste of victory champagne still fresh following the series victory at Lord's on Saturday they now have two ODIs in Aberdeen, the first of which is against Ireland
